en days: who said to Paul through the Spirit, that he should not go up to Jerusalem.","year":60},{"id":"reclrccv1UaW5rHlg","ref":"Acts.21.5","text":"And when we had accomplished those days, we departed and went our way; and they all brought us on our way, with wives and children, till we were out of the city: and we kneeled down on the shore, and prayed.","year":60},{"id":"recL532tNWFxvrJEl","ref":"Acts.21.6","text":"And when we had taken our leave one of another, we took ship; and they returned home again.","year":60},{"id":"rec2ae0u6jILZ84wv","ref":"Acts.21.7","text":"And when we had finished our course from Tyre, we came to Ptolemais, and saluted the brethren, and abode with them one day.","year":60},{"id":"recGBlhN3XQg1Vea1","ref":"Acts.21.8","text":"And the next day we that were of Paul’s company departed, and came unto Caesarea: and we entered into the house of Philip the evangelist, which was one of the seven; and abode with him.","year":60}]}
